				<td colspan="2"><span>I must assume you mean soloing in PoI.  Cause as soon as I hit 46 I sprinted to PoI to try to get in a group.   I found some very generous people how allowed me into their group (maybe they did not realize I was such a low lvl).  I quickly made 47 and 48 in that zone over a couple days of very moderate playing.  It was not easy to get a group, but when I did the exp was great.  
<br />

<br />
Currently, lvl 50, the exp is still good.  I imagine you could swarm or chant kite right at the entrance at lvl 52 if you are alone.  There have been many times where I go to POI to see if I could get in a group and was the only one in the zone.  After reading this thread... I may try to do a little chant kiting in the entrance myself.  (I am bound in PoK, so the CR will not be too long, hehe.)  
<br />

<br />
I do not know the zone very well.  I have been to the entrance and a bit in each direction from there.  Perhaps there are other places in the zone a bard can take advantage of our typical soloing strategies.
<br />

