				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoInnovation<a name="38329"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 12:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I always loved POI.  But I HATED XPing at zone in.  I consider that &quot;What we do until we are all here&quot;.
<br />

<br />
The most fun, and actually safest, way to approach POI is to forget the word &quot;camp&quot;.  Get a porter, a decent tank, and  a decent healer... and a group with reasonable DPS (makeup of that is not important).  Warn any casters that they need to manage their mana well.  Then move forward... always forward... you are racing the backspawn.  Fight a few... move into their spawn area...  fight one...move...fight a couple...move...etc.  There are 2 choices for leaving, fight your way back thru the backspawn, or evac to zone or port out.  
<br />

<br />
Backspawn catching up to you?  Need a med break? One member leaving/being replaced? Cleric dead? ... 
<br />
Evac, med up, rezz in GY if needed, reform if needed, and start in again.  There is no downside to doing so, except if you get a group of regulars that is trying to beat their record of how far in they have gotten.
<br />

<br />
A word of warning:  
<br />
If you are doing the crawlthru, and you see up ahead...
<br />
&quot;Junk Beast&quot;... 
<br />
and you think to yourself, 
<br />
&quot;Hmm I wonder if we could take that with this group...&quot; 
<br />
The answer is a resounding no.. 
<br />
back up a little and cast the evac </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
